title: ESR to sell another commercial building in Sydney's Liverpool
text:
Asia-based logistics real estate group ESR continues its active run in asset sales putting another commercial property on the market, an office building in Sydney's third CBD, Liverpool with a price tag of $50 million.

Just days after selling its jointly owned suburban office building in Mulgrave to Singapore property giant Ascendas REIT, ESR has now listed the 7645sq m office building at 211 Northumberland Street in Liverpool for sale.

ESR wants to sell another property, this time a $50 million Liverpool CBD office tower. Supplied

The building in the Liverpool CBD is fully leased to the NSW Government's Family and Community Services until 2022.

It was purchased by the company as part of the Denison portfolio that came with its acquisition of ASX-listed fund manager Propertylink.

The listing is part of the group's ongoing relinquishment of non-core assets, as it continues to focus on its growing industrial portfolio, selling agents say.
